caption: We got a little bit of everything and overall it was pretty good!! Our favorites were the Nashville Chicken Sandwich, Dharma Fried Chicken Box, and the Cheesy Homies. The only thing we didn’t like were the Rosemary Mashed Potatoes because there was wayyyy too much rosemary and it was the only thing we could taste. The Mac and Cheeses were decent but the Buffalo Mac was our fav! Overall there was a great selection to choose from and we’d definitely order again!!
Best vegan food around, the chili dog and burger are phenomenal. I would highly recommend giving this place a try, vegan or not.
Very very good food I show all my friends it when I can to show them vegan food can taste amazing  too

Delicious food! Had their fried green tomato sandwich and mac n cheese you would not believe it is all Vegan! Also have had their BBQ pulled Jackfruit sandwich and it is so good, great texture and flavor.
Food takes longer than the other places, but it's worth it. Unique flavors that work. All vegetarian. Really fun food.

The burger was the best I've had ever. So juicy and it had a little sausage flavor too. The Mac n cheez was amazing. I also ordered 2 desserts and let me just say they did not make it home. I drove an hour to check this place out as where I live there are very few, to no vegan restaurants. I was so pleased.
Portion was small. I ordered dfc but I didn't like Potato salad was too cold. I ordered cheese cake brownie but it wasn't good. I threw it away. Staff was nice. Sorry.

I ordered the Brew Burger with a side of mac and cheese with an extra side of Cheesy Homies. The burger was a blend of beyond meats seasoned well covered in a tangy sauce and small dills. It was delicious. I was not a fan of the macaroni and cheese, but the cheesy homies were very tasty.  There was a misunderstanding due to the menu on the app Doordash and I had previously left a 3 star review based mainly on frustration about the clarity of the menu. After some very good communication with Samantha I deleted my prior review. I think 4.5 stars would be appropriate. Given that I can either choose 4 or 5, I chose 5 because of the earnest communication and the care in preparation. Just because my taste buds do not align with one of the sides is not reason enough to dip to 4. I recommend and will continue to explore their menu.

Everything I tried today was so very flavorful. I ordered all of my items for takeout and the food was ready in no more than 10 minutes. It look just like the many photos that I have found online. The person who took my order over the phone was so patient with spectacular customer service. In closing, I will definitely be back.

The Dixie Dharma, Market On South located in Orlando is 30 times better than this one. Originally when my boyfriend and I went, it was great! So good that we both went back. However, from the couple of times that I have been to Dixie Dharma in Armature Works, it’s so inconsistent. Honestly, it’s a 50/50 chance whether it’ll be good or be bad. We kept tryna give it the benefit of the doubt but it’s been bad to the point we no longer go there. We’ve been so disappointed that whats the point even going anymore if in total for the both of us we spend 30 each time and it’s just bad every single time? The one time it was good was from an employee who had great customer service, was very kind, helped us, answered all our questions, gave us samples, had a great energy, and the food came out nice and hot with lots of flavor. Ever since then it’s always been different people. Of course everyone has different times and different shifts but the food has never compared to that one guy during that day. Now? The food has come out bland, not always hot, just not good. I always ended up getting the same meal every single time I went because what’s the point of venturing around the menu when its become more of a 20% chance that I’ll be good. Cute place, yes it’s vegan, but no I’ve been disappointed one to manny times to go back. I’d rather travel to Dixie Dharma, Market On South all day instead of the one in Tampa.

So many options. Was something for all of us. Great vegan food. Even the non vegans we're eating with us this time. Thank you for all the options. Much appreciate the creativity, the work and all that goes into making vegan. You nailed it!
Their vegan fried chicken is better than “real” chicken.
The fried chicken is phenomenal 😍😋 I wish I could give it 10/5 stars! Also there wasn’t much of a line and service was fast. :)
Vegan BBQ! It was soooo good! Whenever you want to open an Omaha restaurant we’re here :)

This is the best vegan/vegetarian food I’ve ever had. I had the “fried chick’n” with garlic mac n cheese. Everything was SO flavorful and really balanced. Even my meat eating partner loved all of it. Some of the best mac n cheese i’ve ever had. Sad I don’t live closer to here, but I highly recommend it!

Me and several other groups of customers waited in line for a few minutes only to find out that no new orders would be accepted.no worries because I had already placed an order right? no they canceled it without notifying me and I drove all the way there just to find out. Really dropped the ball on this one guys, where's management?
Delicious. Vindaloo Mac was bomb.

Best vegan food I have had in tampa! Food is extremely well seasoned and so flavorful. Also very fairly priced with generous portions! I have made it my life goal to replicate their chili dog recipe 😅
starting to change my diet iwas looking for  healthy food that tastes good and the burrito they had the was amazing
Poot customer service probably first vegan restaurant that is not friendly.
Love the food

This was my first experience here and it was amazing and filled with flavor. My friend and I got 2 of the meals so we both can try a little of what they had to offer. I look forward to coming back. This is my first time on a vegetarian journey, and I wasn’t let down. I was amazed at how the food tastes just like actual meat and the actual flavor. The customer service was good as they were very patient and friend, and happy to answer all of my question. I left very satisfied.

Ate there for the first time this evening and I’m absolutely OBSESSED! From the entrees to the desserts, hands down one of the best vegan/plant based spots in Tampa. I can’t wait to go back and try something new. The weekends get busy, but the food is totally worth the wait. Also, don’t be afraid to order their sides on their own, they were freaking delicious! I highly suggest giving this place a shot, even if you’re not vegan it’s still worth it! The combination of middle eastern, Asian, and American flavors are stunning, 10/10 would recommend!
Amazing
The DFC BOWL is amazing
My coffee wasn't warm enough.
Cool vibe to this multiple eateries
Ordered a DFC bowl. This was not it. Went there in person to try and get it resolved and they refused to help me. $27 for this meal. Not good portion sizes even with the wrong item.
A great new twist on plant-based. If you’re looking for great southern foods but may have a change to your diet, check them out.
Love Dharma's vegan dishes! A bit pricey but worth it. Wish they had a location closer to Brandon. Maybe one day! 😊
The food was clean, well seasoned and flavorful!!!
soooo good man. best vegan chicken sandwiches around the tampa bay area.
Soooooo good. Loved the DFC Chick'n. Mac n Cheese was awesome too.

Offering home Southern comfort food to satisfy anyone. I'll eat my way through their menu. I started with Carolina BBQ jackfruit sandwich, black-eyed pea salad on the side, and you'll never get that nicey spicey chilli cheez dog away from me! Such good food and friendly, welcoming, helpful service. Y'all gotta try it and get your being re-centered
I really enjoyed my vegan burrito!

Firstly, i don't EVER feel compelled to write a review. BUT...I have been trying to find a decent vegan/vegetarian place for such a long time and ... have found it. My career has allowed me to travel around the world and i purposely seek out vegan/lacto vegetarian food wherever i am the world-I found Tampa sorely lacked a decent place - until now. Being a plant based eater(sometimes a lacto veg) for over 22 years i know that what vegan (and many vegetarian)eateries don't get right is seasoning , knowing what actually tastes good and what is ..good hearty food . Dharma Fine Vittles knows this very well. I believe this is why they are successful and will continue to be so.
Incredibly dank

It was delicious! We ended up going twice on our visit to Tampa. Portion sizes are great, prices are reasonable, and the food is flavorful! Tried the chili dogs, the dfc bowl, wet burrito, burger and they were all fantastic. Decadent vegan food at its finest.

Dharma Fine Vittles at Armature Works is THEE vegan spot to check out in Tampa! The building is a small food hub, but with its vibrant colors and the smells coming from the kitchen, you can’t miss this spot.  The menu has a variety of options from burgers to mac and cheese, making you want to try everything to see if it is good without all the dairy, meat, etc. And delicious it is! We tried the Wet burrito and vegan chocolate peanut butter cookie from Oopsy Daisy.  You order at the counter and they hand you an alarm to notify you when your orders ready. Since it is a food hub you can choose to sit anywhere (inside or out) but you’ll probably want to sit closer to Dharma so you can go back to order some more!

I go to the one in orlando all the time and recently tried this location to see how it compared while I was on a work thing in st pete and holy s*** it sure compares, might even be better. this could have been the cocktails talking. that's a plus
Was requested to pay extra for sauce on a $15 bowl. Food was OK but completely not worth it and the service was subpar.

I ate here for the 1st time yesterday and spent over $100 and tipped the cashier the maximum tip. After paying, I asked the cashier if I could have an extra pack of BBQ sauce and he had the audacity to tell me I had to pay 50¢. I was surprised that he wanted to charge me 50¢ after paying all that money and tipping so generously. Usually when spending this amount of money, most businesses tend to give you complementary items but I didn’t say anything about it. I didn’t have spare change, only bills. So I gave him a bill and he told me that he cannot provide me with change! The food was good but this incident turned me off. Too petty. There are other vegan restaurants in the city that are not like this. I probably won’t eat here again.
Some of the best Vegan food in Tampa.  I have had the chilli dogs and most recently the Dharma Fried Chick'n DFC.  I had the DFC bowl and My wife had the DFC box.  Everything was perfect!
We drove from Land O Lakes to try this vegan place and were definitely impressed. Delicious food and such a variety of menu options.  We will be returning again soon.
We ordered online and our food was suppose to be ready in 10 minutes!  45 minutes later and we are still waiting on our food.

I stop by Dixie Dharma every 6 to 8 weeks while in Tampa. They  have the best vegan food, and trust me, I’m so picky when it comes to food.I’m trying to sample everything on their menu..lol- I wish I had the recipe to their boiled peanuts peanuts because no other place in the world compares to theirs. They are pricey for the amount that you et but they are well worth it..I hope Atlanta gets a Dixie Dharma soon. It will do so well, until then I’m a fan of the one in Tampa.

AHHMAZING food & Huge portions! (You won't leave here hungry that's for sure.)  Hubby & I have enjoyed everything we've ever ordered from here, but today's Dharma Fried Chick'n was undescribably delicious. I would eat here every day if I lived closer.

So so good!!! Buffalo Mac n cheese was packed with flavor!! My boyfriend went to order a sad chicken sandwich from another shop and came back saw my plate, ate from my plate and got up to order from dharma too!!! 10/10 recommend.

My Boyfriend & I ate here for the first time and it was soooo good.  The girl who took our order ( sorry I didn’t get your name) was awesome. Friendly, knowledgeable & very helpful with her recommendations.  Looking forward to our next visit.

I had ordered their wet burrito with a side of the original mac 'n cheese but I also ordered paid for but never got the vegan twinkies. The order was to-go so I didn't notice right away. Food was good but I wish they would have checked before sending me on my way as I don't live in Tampa.
Eshton was awesome and food is amazing. I got a chili dawg and cheesie homies. The vinkies were also great.

Best vegan food ever, I went to this restaurant on a Florida trip last year - I'm french btw, and I keep talking about this place because this is the kind of restaurant we need everywhere to show people that vegan food can be the best food ever when it is made with love, attention and quality! I will be back, for sure!
I get hungry just thinking about this place. Definitely one of my favorite vegan places in Tampa. Delicious every time I visit.
Omg. Amazing food.  Cannot wait to try more menu options
Love, love this place for good vegan comfort food. The brew burger is amazing, Mac n cheese is good and they have 3 different flavors, and their Dixie dippers(vegan chicken tenders) are sooo good.
Great find inside Armature Works, fully plant based and plenty of options to satisfy anyone in your group.

I'm here at armature works everyday almost i love to try new places. I find myself here at Dixie multiple times a week for their Buffalo Mac and cheese. Seriously  out of this world.  The faux chicken as well on their Buffalo sandwich is fire thed staff is very knowledgeable in helping me find a selection for someone like me who dosnt eat vegan .. 10 out of 10 would recommend and im not anything close to vegan.

It was my first time eating 100% vegan/plant based food and WOW! I was blown away. My only concern going into trying vegan food was how the texture of the “meats”would be. I had the Carolina BBQ pulled jack fruit and WOWOWOWOWOW! I loved it so much! Flavor and texture was on point! I had it with a side of Mac and “cheese” and it was amazing! We loved it so much we went back the next day. Can’t wait to keep trying their other menu options. Biscuit and gravy will surely be next.
LOVE THIS PLACE! They have the perfect combination of light vegan food mixed with nice comfort food.
Fried Green Tomato Sandwich is the best! Great staff and location inside of Armature Works!

The food was delicious, the staff was super friendly and I can't wait to go back again! Best BBQ E-V-E-R! The sandwich was very flavorful and their buffalo mac and cheese was out of this world!! We'll be back for sure!!
I was told they are open til 10pm but they had closed before 9pm and we drove all the way to this place :(

Would have been pretty ok if anything had any salt on it. If you want to try it, bring some salt packets.  The traditional "creamy" Mac n cheese had no sauce. It was just noodles with some seasonings and a garnish of veggies on top. I seriously wonder if they forgot to put sauce on it.
Get the Hawt Chick'n when it's available. It's da bomb. Everything is flavorful and best of all:  Vegan!  Win win win  Love it!
Best food I've ever had. Absolutely perfect!
Not a vegan, but tried with vegan friend.  Excellent tasting food regardless. The orange bird was really good.
Really delicious food! I got the pulled jackfruit sandwich with buffalo mac & cheese. Only complaint is that I wish the portions were larger since it’s pretty pricey.
Great food every time! Making it a point to try everything on the menu.
This is the best vegan food in Tampa period .
Food was delicious.
I had the Brew Burger it was pretty good and tasted just like a burger! The boiled peanut were pretty good too. I would definitely go back and try other items on the menu.
Amazing!
Tiny portions, very overpriced. Very creative dishes. Interesting menu. Food is very good tasting.

Great tasty vegan spot. Just try the Hillbilly chili cheese dogs! The bbq sandwiches are good, just overly saucy for me. I liked them though. All the sides are good but I will say I’m on Essex with the crispy brussel sprouts and cheesy home fries.
Wow this place have fantastic food with an unmatchable ambiance
Fast and friendly service and a variety of items to choose from on the menu
Delicious vegan food! Erica at the front was very friendly and nice. So glad this was added to the food choices at Heights Market.
Great options. Good food.
Delicious biscuits and gravy and grits! And the best customer service ever...what a great place. I rarely post my opinion; I was ultra impressed.
Still some of the best vegan food I have ever had!!!!
Their fried green tomatoes are to die for, but this last time I ordered the sloppy joe and the sauce they use was nauseatingly sweet and just way too much sauce to begin with.
First time here....the Brussel sprouts were amazing, as well as the Buffalo Mac n cheese and the vegan dogs.  Too bad I'm from out of town, otherwise this would be my favorite lunch spot!

Food was good. Deducting two stars because the guy at the counter was not the most inviting.  I heard great things about Armature,  so I decided to drive from Orlando to check things out.  There was a couple in front of me and they went left straight to the register instead of going around since nobody besides me was there at the moment. Guy took there order. When it was my turn to take my order, he made me go all the way around.  Not sure what his problem was because he could have told before he took that couple's order rather than letting me stand there for 10min. then have me walk around for no reason since nobody was there when I was waiting. Felt like I was living a Seinfeld episode. Probably will not make the 2 hour trip there.

Visited Dixie Dharma in Tampa for the second time. The food was excellent! If you’re new to vegan, you could start with something easy like the hillbilly chili dawgs. My favorite is the orange bird. This place is def worth trying for your stubborn carcass munching  friends. Talk them into trying a plant based meal with you. I’ve also visited the location in Orlando and it’s just as good. We’ve always been greeted with super friendly customer service. They gladly answer any menu related questions.
It was good but expensive.

Amazing vegan restaurant! We ordered the Orange Bird, Florida Fried Green Tomato, original Creamy Cashew Max n Cheese, and Crispy Brussels!  The food was super yummy and decently filling. My favorite was the Mac and cheese!  The atmosphere of the market is cool, young, and very social. It was fun to eat food here and grab drinks after.
Dixie Dharma vegan -grub-.
Amazing food! We loved everything. It was great to see boiled peanuts on a menu

Lady in the front was so friendly and understanding. Food came out quick and it was the best chili dog I’ve ever had, pleasantly surprised by the entire dish including how beautiful and fresh the garnishing was. my thanks to their head chef Ashley Simmons.

This Sunday We went from lunch with a friend We waited for 45 minutes in line finally get to the cashier to order the guy at the counter was super rude he Embarrassed me in front of everyone and And refills to substitute something that I’m allergic to in the meal
Service was great and the fried green tomato sandwich and potato salad
Really good food. Great vegan options. Staff was really nice and friendly.
Very good!! Had biscuits and gravy with cheesy hommies - flavorful and well prepared. Definitely will go back.

This place is absolutely amazing. I have now tried almost all their items and every single items stands out!! They really put their heart, soul and talent in the food they make. Their weekly specials are amazing. So far best entree is Hilly Chilly Dawgs and premium side Cheesy Homies is perfect (nothing matches to this!)
If I were to be held at gun point with my wallet in one hand, and my dixie dharma take out box in the other... I would make a DMV appointment first thing in the morning...
Amazing delicious innovative vegan food
We tried a little bit of everything and loved the flavors
Friendly staff, same great food as the original location in a cool hip venue.

First of all, the young lady who was working the front was very delightful, cheerful, and helpful. She helped us pick out the perfect meal for lunch. This is a plant based food court business. And we were very happy to find such a place where they actually know how to cook plant based comfort food. We had difficulty choosing between the barbeque sandwich or the chili dogs. Next time we are there, we're definitely going to try them.  Oh, and after we ordered we wandered around a little bit. She offered to text us when our meal was ready! That was an unexpected perk for us so we wouldn't have to just stand there waiting for the food. I highly recommend this place.
Great vegetarian breakfast burrito! Wouldn’t even notice there’s not meat and great grits
Amazing food, the best meal I've had in Tampa yet! A great combo of flavors and styles.
I passionately loved their plantains with black beans in a delicious cuban flare!  I'm still thinking about how amazing this food was to the senses!
Nice place to hang out. Looks like old industrial area. Place has vegan options for everything meat could offer

Just had the pulled Jackfruit sandwich and collards. Yeah man. I mean, i made that thing disappear. I live in St Pete, and I’ll be making the trip back across the bridge just to eat here again. Super friendly service too.
Happy to have a location in Tampa, I usually drive 2 hours to Orlando.
Incredible food. Had the jackfruit special and the regular menu on. Both were amazing.
So so good! I had the Heirloom Tomato TLT & the original mac n cheese and it was def the closest to mac n cheese I’ve had since going vegan! The prices are also super reasonable :) will be back
Very hard to explain why Dixie Dharmas food is so bleh but my kale salad taste like acid... and everything else was horrible unfortunately

They have mastered the seitan vegan bacon.  The flavor of the bacon is crisp with a rich texture. The flavor of barbeque surrounds your taste buds and leaves with a ligh tsweet finish.   This is a must try for anyone who appreciates cutting edge delicious food.
Food was good and the people were nice...
I cannot say enough good things about this place. Their breakfast or lunch is always so good and the staff is always so friendly. So happy I found it and wilI come back every chance I get.
The food is to die for! Everything I've tried here is amazing. Must try the biscuits and gravy and the fried green tomato sandwich!! The staff is always so friendly and helpfu.100% recommend.
Kind of pricey but great service and good food.
Good vegan options if you like try something unique. For me it was a bit too tangy and salty.

Mouth watering deliciousness!! Best food you can get! I recommend everyone to eat here all the time! My husband and I would go to the Orlando location and complain only about the drive because it was so far away and was like a days trip for us. But the food was too good to complain. Now there’s one in Tampa!! Which is a lot closer for us and we still get to enjoy some yummies!!  Only thing I ask is please come to Sarasota!!!!

Great Food and friendly staff!! I didnt know what to tey because there was soo many choices and the beautiful young ladies were more than willing to help me~ love this place, great vine ,vegan friendly and always a warm welcome!!
Very friendly and quick service. The food was very filling, huge portions, and delicious!! I had the chili cheese dog and the buffalo mac and cheese. I would recommend Dixie Dharma.

So delicious!!! This was my first time here and ordered the fried green tomato sandwich with creole butter grits and my husband got the chili dogs with cheesy home fries. This is not fast food so it will take a moment to make but nothing too long. The cashier was sooo nice and helpful since it was our first time. I want to keep eating that sandwich it was so good. If you're here, please give them a try. Did I mention our meal was completely vegan?
This place is amazing. Food will put you in one of those indacouch moments. The dankest of Brussels over here will definitely be back for some more;)

Dixie Dharma is a tasty vegan eatery located in Heights Public Market. On. Visit to Tampa, I ordered the Wet Burrito (Jackfruit carnitas, tofu scramble, homefries, black bean mash, guacamole, florida sweet corn, pickled red onion, smothered with tomato gravy) with a side of watermelon salad. My meal was made to order and tasted very fresh. I enjoyed my meal, but I felt it was a little over priced.
loved the vegan options.

Get the Orange Bird. DO IT. Everything here is amazing, the Mac N Cheese, the sandwiches and hot dogs, sides and salads WOW.  Vegan southern food that tastes amazing everyone veg or not would love. <3

Stop everything and go here now. Sooo good. Destiny helped me choose and I landed in Nirvana.  In case it's not onvious to you (it wasn't to me), this is a food hall style place with a bunch of options, so good for an Omni double date
Thrilled about another vegan place to choose from. People and the presentation are awesome. I want to try the bbq jackfruit and orange bird next time

Very vegan friendly, beautiful presentation.  Food was spectacular and the service was wonderful. Great place to go when you want to be healthy, but still cheat on your diet. The best of both worlds. Doesn't taste processed or frozen.

Hi there! I am here to tell you about the orange bird. It is delicious, best bbq in the bay area! (faux or not) Git up on over there and eat some food! These are the FINE VITTLES u are lookin' for. I use to drive to Orlando just to eat here! I have eaten everything on the menu and nothing dissapoints!  I even get excited about that salad and everyone knows you don't win friends with salad. Buffalo mac is a dream come true, so are the biscuits and gravy! The grits are the best too. It is a great time to be alive! Thx Dixie Dharma :)
